<a href="javascript:card_browser(104)">Blade Tip</a> x2 <br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(103)">Black Breath</a> x2 <br>
Ulaire Enquea x2 <br>
Ulaire Nelya, Twilight x2 <br>
Ulaire Cantea x2 <br>
Ulaire Lemenya x2 <br>
Ulaire Attea x2 <br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(113)">Nazgul Sword</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(112)">Morgul Gates</a> <br>
Bill Ferny <br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(33)">Saruman&#39;s Power</a> <br>
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Bid 6 to go first. Start Green Dragon and pull Sam. Kill Sam off early on.<br>
<br>
The fellowship is pretty simple. Keep the twilight pool low, never more than 3 in the fellowship phase. The trickiest part of the fellowship is figuring out when to play the Pathfinders. By matchups I recommend them as follows (if drawn):<br>
Nazgul - Sites 4, 7, and 9<br>
Urukhai - Sites 3 and 7<br>
Moria - Site 6 and 7<br>
Sauron - Someone still plays that? Hmmm... probably 4, 7, and 8.<br>
<br>
Notice the heavy dependence on a Pathfinder on 7. If it is obvious that your opponent relies heavily on allies and archery don&#39;t worry about calling it. Otherwise do. Also depending on the popularity of Moria or Ferny decks in your area you might want to add in two Aragorn&#39;s Bow.<br>
<br>
The shadow needs to keep your opponent behind you. Your opponent should feel a continual ominous presence that if they move again their going to get hurt badly. Use your Abandoning Reasons to get rid of The Balrog&#39;s Swords after the Bridge or to dump your fellowship if your opponent looks prepared to make the end run. Ideally, you want to fellowship win, but your Shadow will do the job more times than you might think. Make sure and Beyond The Height their armor off of Boromir at site 4 if neccesary. Wouldn&#39;t want the Balrog to go hungry would you?<br>
<br>
Anyways, all comments are welcome and appreciated. I&#39;m more interested in how people think this deck will fair at larger tournaments (GenCon, Worlds) than at local level. Assume that out of 8 games this deck will face 5 Urukhai, 2 Nazgul, and 1 random crap. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=24910"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=24910" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
